### 1. Create a New Election (Admin Only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/elections
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "title": "Student Council Elections 2026",
  "description": "Annual voting for the main student body representatives.",
  "startDate": "2026-02-11T08:00:00Z",
  "endDate": "2026-02-15T17:00:00Z",
  "status": "upcoming"
}

### 2. Get All Elections (Any Authenticated User)
GET {{baseUrl}}/elections
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 3. Filter Elections by Status
# Options: upcoming, voting, completed, cancelled
GET {{baseUrl}}/elections/filter?status=upcoming
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 4. Get Election by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/elections/{{electionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 5. Update Election (Admin Only)
# Note: You can send partial data
PUT {{baseUrl}}/elections/{{electionId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "title": "UPDATED: Student Council Elections 2026",
  "description": "Revised schedule for the main student body representatives."
}

### 6. Change Election Status Manually (Admin Only)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/elections/{{electionId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "status": "voting"
}

### 7. Delete Election (Admin Only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/elections/{{electionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}